						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">On the face of a broken pillar set up on the bund of the well outside the village.</hi></p>						

						<p>Tribhuvanamalla (Vikramāditya VI)—A.D. 1107.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated <hi rend="bold">Chālukya-Vikrama year 32, Sarvajit, Ās11vayuja, Amāvāsyā solar eclipse, Wednesday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1107, October 16, Wednesday, f.d.t. ·98.</hi> No eclipse, however, occurred on that day.</p>						

						<p>The inscription is badly damaged and seems to record a gift of toll-incomes, for the benefit of god Sōmanātha, by Suṅkaverggaḍe Mādhava-Sēnādhipati, Heggaḍe Mādeyanāyaka and others.</p>						

